@startuml 03-multi-device-registration
title Device Self-Enrollment Flow

skinparam backgroundColor #FEFEFE
skinparam roundcorner 10
skinparam shadowing false

skinparam sequence {
    ArrowColor #1976D2
    LifeLineBorderColor #1976D2
    ParticipantBackgroundColor #E3F2FD
    ParticipantBorderColor #1976D2
}

actor "User\n(New Device)" as user
participant "New Device\nExtension" as newDev
participant "S3" as s3

== Step 1: Install & Configure ==

user -> newDev : Install extension
user -> newDev : Configure cloud provider\n(QR code / config file / manual entry)
user -> newDev : Enter master password\n+ secret key

== Step 2: Generate Device Keys ==

newDev -> newDev : Generate Device ID (UUID)
newDev -> newDev : Generate Ed25519 keypair\n(signing)
newDev -> newDev : Generate ECDH P-256 keypair\n(key exchange)

note right of newDev
    **New Device Keys:**
    - deviceSignKeyPair (Ed25519)
    - deviceEcdhKeyPair (P-256)
end note

== Step 3: Download & Verify Vault ==

newDev -> s3 : Download vault
s3 --> newDev : Signed envelope

newDev -> newDev : Verify envelope signature\n(Ed25519)

== Step 4: Unwrap VaultKey via Secret Key ==

newDev -> newDev : Find secret key slot\n(type: "secret-key")
newDev -> newDev : Unwrap VaultKey from\nsecret key slot

note right of newDev
    **Secret Key Slot (A256GCMKW):**
    1. Import secret key as AES-256 CryptoKey
    2. AES-GCM unwrap → VaultKey
end note

== Step 5: Self-Register ==

newDev -> newDev : Create own ECDH device\nkey slot (wrapping VaultKey)
note right of newDev
    **ECDH-ES+A256GCMKW:**
    1. Generate ephemeral P-256 keypair
    2. ECDH: ephemeral.priv + own.pub
    3. ConcatKDF(shared) → KEK
    4. AES-GCM wrap VaultKey
end note

newDev -> newDev : Add self to device registry\n(deviceId, name, public keys,\nenvironment, location)

== Step 6: Persist & Upload ==

newDev -> newDev : Derive MasterKEK from password
newDev -> newDev : Wrap device private keys\nwith MasterKEK
newDev -> newDev : Sign updated envelope\n(Ed25519)

newDev -> s3 : Upload updated vault
s3 --> newDev : 200 OK

newDev -> newDev : Store wrapped keys +\ndevice state in IndexedDB
newDev -> newDev : secureWipe(secretKey,\npasswordBuffer)

newDev --> user : Setup complete!\nVault accessible

note right of newDev
    **No existing device needed.**
    User only needs:
    - Master password (memorized)
    - Secret key (paper backup)
    - Cloud config (QR/file/manual)
end note

legend right
    **Self-Enrollment:**
    New devices unwrap VaultKey
    from the secret key slot and
    create their own device slot.
    Existing devices see the new
    device on their next sync.
endlegend

@enduml
